# Styling Rules - Hacker News (Y Combinator) Old-School Style

## When to Apply These Rules

**ALWAYS apply these styling rules when:**
- Creating or modifying CSS/Tailwind styles
- Designing new UI components (buttons, forms, tables, cards, etc.)
- Writing inline styles or className attributes
- Updating global styles in `globals.css` or theme files
- Implementing layout and spacing
- Adding colors, typography, or visual effects
- Building responsive designs
- Working on any frontend styling-related code

**These rules take precedence over:**
- Default Tailwind styling conventions
- Modern UI design trends (gradients, shadows, animations)
- Any conflicting style guidelines unless explicitly overridden by the user

**Exception:** Only deviate from these rules if the user explicitly requests a different styling approach or specific design that conflicts with these guidelines.

